## Tool Permissions

The parallel-explore skill uses read-only analysis tools:
- `read`: View file contents across threads
- `grep_search`: Parallel pattern searches
- `file_search`: Concurrent file discovery
- `list_dir`: Directory traversal
- `glob`: Pattern-based file matching

**Denied**: `edit`, `bash`, `write` (no modifications)

## Guidelines

- Partition exploration tasks to maximize parallelism
- Avoid redundant work across threads
- Merge results with deduplication
- Report thread status for observability
- Coordinate with base explore skill for focused analysis
- Use efficient partitioning strategies based on codebase structure
- Set reasonable thread limits to avoid resource exhaustion
- Prioritize threads for incremental results delivery
- Handle thread failures gracefully with partial results
- Cache thread results for re-aggregation if needed

